title: Foreclosure Needs Scores by ZIP Code, West Virginia, 11.4.2008
name: Foreclosure Needs Scores by ZIP Code, West Virginia, 11.4.2008
description:
"This dataset displays various foreclosure needs scores by zip code for the state of West Virginia as of 11.4.2008. The scores were created to help state and local governments identify areas of greatest need for Neighborhood Stabilization Program (NSP) funding, LISC researchers calculated a foreclosure needs score for most US ZIP Codes that incorporates factors specified in the authorizing legislation. 

The data includes: state, zip, place name, county, Intrastate Foreclosure Needs Score, Ratio of Local Vacancy Rate to State Rate, Capped Vacancy Ratio, Intrastate Subprime Component Score, Intrastate Foreclosure Component Score, Intrastate Delinquency Component Score. Definitions for all of these attributes can be found in the attribute descriptions.
For more information, such as how the scores were calculated please refer to the weblinks provided in the metadata.
Geographic Note: All ZIP Codes with less than 10 total weighted loans were removed before initial and final scores were calculated. In addition, PO Box and Unique ZIP Codes were not included in final calculations. 
"
